  "content":"Melissa Bowen is the principal investigator of the project.\nShe is a physical oceanographer who works on understanding the ocean from the global overturning circulation to estuaries. Over the last several decades, her main research focus is understanding how the ocean around New Zealand is changing.\n"},{
