  "content":"Peter is a Senior Principal Research Scientist at CSIRO, Australia, specialising in ocean data assimilation, ocean forecasting, ocean observing, and ocean dynamics.\nHe leads the Australian Argo Program and was a long-term contributor to the Bluelink Ocean Forecasting Australia Partnership. Peter developed the data assimilation system that underpinned Australia\u0026rsquo;s first operational ocean forecast system and Australia\u0026rsquo;s first eddy-resolving global ocean reanalysis.\nPeter\u0026rsquo;s particularly interested in better understanding the physical oceanography of the waters around Australia, and developing tools and products to support marine industries. Peter\u0026rsquo;s current research focus includes development of data-driven ocean forecasting capabilities on National and Global scales for National, civilian benefit.\n"},{
